President Obama has declared a major disaster in the state of New Mexico due to flooding that occurred from June 22 to July 12, 2012. Federal aid will be provided to assist with recovery efforts in the affected areas, including the counties of Lincoln and Sandoval and the Santa Clara Pueblo. Funding will be available for emergency work, facility repairs, and hazard mitigation measures. Nancy M. Casper has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations. Further designations may be made based on damage assessments. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.